    {
      "id": "focus-layout-local-fragments",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Local Fragment Insertion Point",
      "position": {
        "x": 900,
        "y": 380
      },
      "width": 440,
      "height": 300,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "# Local Fragment Insertion Point\n\nThe most immediate use of semantic zoom may not be graph-to-graph traversal.\n\nIt may be **within a single local graph**, using fragments as units of reveal.\n\nThat means:\n\n- reduce on-screen density without deleting meaning\n- keep one graph exploratory instead of statically overloaded\n- let nearby fragments sit in `summary`\n- let deeper fragments collapse to `icon` or hint state\n\nDefault split:\n\n- local fragments come in at medium detail / `summary`\n- external graphs come in as `icon`\n\nThis is likely the right insertion point for semantic zoom in Twilite's own home/root surfaces.",
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "markdown",
          "sourceRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
          "ref": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
          "identity": {
